If P is here more original, we must suppose that the passage was omitted from C in view of some performance of the play at a time when the topical allusion to Harvey had lost point.

It is however possible that if the play was performed several times within a few years, fresh Harvey allusions would be added. The above passage is therefore not very convincing as to C's infe- riority. With it goes probably another, at the end of the play, 1. 2934.
